- These are your first steps in a bigger world: the ideal place for learning how to work in a big corporation; 

- Excellent salaries;

- The best HR I could hope to find. Really, these guys are always trying to create a positive environment and a feeling of belonging.  Even if the Chinese touch of some initiatives could seem strange to Western employees, I was pleasantly surprised by their continuous, positive efforts;

- Buy the ticket, enjoy the ride: a lot of work is waiting for you, but this will help you to improve quickly. You will learn how to be organized (a pivotal and criminally underrated skill) in order to  manage all your daily tasks.

- Knowledge: there is a treasure to be found in terms  of strategic topics to master. The expertise gained  will make you a more desirable candidate for other companies;

-Mentorship: if you find the right mentor, your probation will become an uplifting experience;

- Curiosity: the close encounter of the third kind with the Chinese corporate culture will force you to question your certainties about this, improving your openness;

cons:
- No remote working at all;
- The first encounter with the  "Chinese way" of doIng things may be a harsh one or not, depending from your openness to change;
- Some procedures seem to be unnecessarily complicated;
- If you want to work from 9 AM to 5 PM and have a career as well, maybe this is not your place;

